Package: qgis-x11-postgresql
Version: 0.6.0
Revision: 1
Description: Qt/X11-based GIS (no GRASS support)
License: GPL
Homepage: http://www.qgis.org
Maintainer: BABA Yoshihiko <babayoshihiko@mac.com>
DescDetail: << 
Qt/X11-based Geographical Information System (no GRASS support) supports
PostgreSQL, but Fink version of PostgreSQL does not contain PostGIS.
<<
DescUsage: Just type 'qgis' at the command prompt inside an X environment.

# Dependencies.
Depends: qt3-shlibs (>=3.1.2), libgeos2-shlibs (>=2.0), gdal-shlibs (>=1.2.3), proj (>=4), postgresql80 (>=8.0.2-11) | postgresql80-ssl (>=8.0.2-11), postgresql80-shlibs (>=8.0.2-11) | postgresql80-ssl-shlibs (>=8.0.2-11)
BuildDepends: qt3 (>=3.1.2), libgeos2 (>=2.0), gdal-dev (>=1.2.3), postgresql80-dev (>=8.0.2-11) | postgresql80-ssl-dev (>=8.0.2-11)
Conflicts: qgis-x11
Replaces: qgis-x11

# Unpack Phase.
Source: mirror:sourceforge:/qgis/qgis-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: ee3f94201837c5aef204e30250991295

# Compile Phase.
GCC: 3.3
ConfigureParams: --with-x --with-qtdir=%p --with-gdal=%p/bin/gdal-config --with-geos=%p/bin/geos-config --with-postgresql=%p/bin --without-grass
CompileScript: ./configure %c; make

# Install Phase.
InstallScript: make install DESTDIR=%d
DocFiles: AUTHORS ChangeLog COPYING README TODO

DescPort: <<
qgis-0.6.0 works with PostgreSQL 7.4 and above, yet Fink version of PostgreSQL 
has PostGIS since 8.0.2-11.

<<